The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro LFS_UNLOCK(cfg) is defined as ((void)cfg), so the statement LFS_UNLOCK(lfs->cfg); becomes an expression-statement that evaluates lfs->cfg and does nothing. This statement is reachable and executed, but removing it would not affect program behaviour in this configuration (no side-effects), therefore it constitutes dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
